CORPORATE SOCIAL RESPONSIBILITY
Belmond is deeply committed to the communities at our worldwide destinations. We are also strongly aware of our responsibility towards natural resources and the environment, especially at locations close to World Heritage Sites.




All our hotels, trains and river cruises run initiatives to support the places and people that surround them. As part of our “Think Global, Act Local” approach we:Purchase as much food as possible from sustainable sourcesRun and support educational programmesFollow sustainable practices to reduce the impact of our operations on the environment and to ensure energy efficiency



Examples that embrace these aims include: 


Belmond Hotel das Cataratas in Brazil’s Iguassu National Park supports an ecology school and a project to protect endangered jaguars and pumas.





Belmond Road to Mandalay and Belmond Orcaella, our Myanmar river cruisers, have helped to build and run more than 20 schools and clinics along their routes thanks to the generous contributions of both staff and guests. It is 20 years since we first began operating cruises in Myanmar and we will celebrate in December with a fund-raising anniversary cruise.





Belmond Palacio Nazarenas in Cusco, Peru, works with local farmers to source unusual ingredients for its kitchens at fair trade prices. Dairy products and flowers come from an organic farm nearby.





Belmond Charleston Place runs Feed the Need and Teach the Need programmes to help homeless and low-income people access nutritious food and train high school students in hospitality skills.





The Eastern & Oriental Express train in Southeast Asia has hosted a “Tiger Express” journey that raised £27,700 for UK charity Save Wild Tigers. The funds will help to protect this threatened species native to the rainforest along the train’s route.












Media Centre







Current initiatives

Every Belmond product, be it an iconic city hotel or our lodge at Machu Picchu, is profoundly respectful of its community and environment. 
Over the years we have constantly undertaken initiatives to ensure that we tread lightly and indeed make a positive contribution to the many destinations where our company operates around the world. 
 Among our many initiatives, the food and beverage operations of the majority of Belmond’s products are assessed by the UK-based Sustainable Restaurant Association. Belmond is the first global luxury hospitality brand to have undertaken this third party testing.
Please explore our website to view our many other activities. Do return to stay updated as more are added over the coming months.
























